Package de.oth.blocklib.world.environment

Class EnvironmentManager

java.lang.Object
de.oth.blocklib.world.environment.EnvironmentManager
public class EnvironmentManager
extends java.lang.Object
Manager managing all of the environment systems like the Skybox, Sun & Moon, Clouds and Weather Holds one entity for every kind of environmental feature, except for CloudClusters, which it holds a list of.
Author:
Sven Kalle SoSe2018

    • PARTICLE_COMPUTE_SHADER_DISPATCH_MULTIPLIER

      private static final int PARTICLE_COMPUTE_SHADER_DISPATCH_MULTIPLIER
      Helps defining how many particles are created. This is important, as the amount of particles existent have to exactly equal the amount of ComputeShader instances dispatched and the size of the array has to be set accordingly. Default is 256, and the value has to equal the 'local_size' set in the ComputeShader.
      See Also:
      Constant Field Values

    • PRECIPITATION_STRENGTH_MULTIPLIER

      private static final int PRECIPITATION_STRENGTH_MULTIPLIER
      Multiplier defining how many particles are spawned. Default is 16.
      See Also:
      Constant Field Values

      public EnvironmentManager​(BlocklibExecutorService executor)
      Constructor sets all of the default values, initializes CloudCLuster List maxParticleAmount gets calculated once as the maximal amount of particles that can be spawned. This prevents that the Array has to be created and filled multiple times throughout the program. OpenGL

    • update

      public void update​(float deltaTime)
      During the update method, the CloudClusters are moved and removed if all clouds despawned. The sunAndMoon Billboard is set to its correct position.

    • draw

      private void draw()

    • initialize

      public void initialize()
      Method used for initializing all of the entities and adding them to the MasterRenderer. Can not be done in the Constructor, because the Manager gets created before OpenGL is ready to add the Renderable Objects.

    • setCurrentWeather

      public void setCurrentWeather​(EnvironmentManager.WeatherTypes weather)
      Method changes the weather to the passed type and sets variables as necessary. Variables meaning the lightBrightness, the maximal amount of CloudClusters, as well as the Precipitation. The Particle array is filled after RAIN or SNOW are set, if no other precipitation was active before, so the particles are at the player's position.
      Parameters:
      weather - Type of Weather to be set to.

    • spawnCloud

      private void spawnCloud()
      Adds CloudClusters to the list until the maxmimum amount of CloudClusters is reached.

      public void setPrecipitationStrength​(int precipitationStrength)
      Set the precipitationStrength. Guaranteed to be within the following bounds:
      [1 ; MAX_PRECIPITATION_STRENGTH]

    • fillParticleArray

      public void fillParticleArray()
      Fills the particle array with random positions around the camera, only if the array is not filled yet. This method is used so that the first random positions only get created when the rain is used for the first time.
